{"id":"math120-deriv_product210-001","cid":"MATH 120","topic":"Derivatives Rules","subtopic":"Product rule","difficulty":2,"license":"CC BY-NC-SA (Numberbender original)","instruction":"Use the product rule to differentiate f(x) = ({a}x + {b})({c}x + {d}). Find f'({x_val}).","params":{"a":{"type":"int","min":1,"max":4},"b":{"type":"int","min":1,"max":6},"c":{"type":"int","min":1,"max":4},"d":{"type":"int","min":1,"max":6},"x_val":{"type":"int","min":0,"max":3}},"answer_expr":"deriv_product210","steps":["u = {a}x+{b}, v = {c}x+{d}. u' = {a}, v' = {c}.","f'(x) = u'v + uv' = {a}({c}x+{d}) + {c}({a}x+{b}).","f'({x_val}) = {a}({v_at}) + {c}({u_at}) = {answer_deriv_product210}."],"tags":["survey-calculus","derivative","product-rule"]}
